{{Quote|It's also a colonial issue, since the Yuuzhan Vong are affecting everyone, and that's overseen by the&mdash;''"<br />"''The Csapla, yes. Your sources are correct, whoever they are.|Luke Skywalker and Jagged Fel|<ref name="Remnant">''[[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic I: Remnant]]''</ref>}}
The '''Csapla family''', also called '''House Csapla''', was a [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] [[Ruling Families/Legends|Ruling Family]] responsible for colonial affairs, agriculture, and distribution of natural resources<ref name="The Chiss" /> throughout the [[Chiss Ascendancy/Legends|Chiss Ascendancy]].<ref name="The Unknown Regions" /> Of these responsibilites, distribution of resources to the Chiss [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] of [[Csilla/Legends|Csilla]] the twenty eight colonies of Chiss Space was the most important.<ref name="The Chiss" /> The [[Chiss family/Legends|family]]'s homeworld was the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Cioral/Legends|Cioral]]. Though heavily [[City/Legends|urbanized]], it was from here that House Csapla managed the Ascendancy's half-dozen agricultural colonies.<ref name="The Essential Atlas" />

In [[28 ABY/Legends|28 ABY]], after five other Ruling Families fell from power, Csapla maintained the Chiss Ascendancy alongside the [[Inrokini family|Inrokini]], [[Sabosen family|Sabosen]] and [[Nuruodo family|Nuruodo]] families. During the [[Yuuzhan Vong War|war]] with the [[Yuuzhan Vong]]<ref name="Remnant" /> around that same time,<ref name="The Essential Readers Companion">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''</ref> when [[Hunt for Zonama Sekot|seeking information]] about Chiss knowledge of [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]] and their hopes of strengthening ties between the Chiss and the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances]]; [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[Mara Jade Skywalker]] asked [[Jagged Fel]] for any contacts among the Csapla and other three Ruling Families who could help them to those ends. Fel refused to answer the question, on the grounds that [[Gender/Legends|he]] did not know who in each family held the rank to assist with the [[Skywalker family/Legends|Skywalker's]] requests and was unwilling to provide the information even if he did.<ref name="Remnant" />

{{Chiss-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The Csapla family was first mentioned in the ''[[The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Chiss]]'', a [[2001]] article in [[Star Wars Gamer 5|''Star Wars Gamer'' 5]] written by [[Juan Schwartz]].<ref name="The Chiss" />

